<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Addresses Spanish Business Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
on Friday urged Chinese and Spanish businesses to strengthen their
cooperation so as to bring bilateral economic and trade relations
to a new level.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to more than 300 Spanish businessmen, Li said that the
good political relations between the two countries have provided
the conditions for their friendly cooperation in every fields.
</P>
<P>
He said that there is a great potential for closer bilateral
economic and trade cooperation. He hoped the business community
will fully tap it.
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed the businessmen on the areas where investments
are greatly encouraged by the Chinese government. With joint
efforts, he said, Sino-Spanish economic and trade relations will
grow from strength to strength.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived in Madrid on Wednesday for a four-day official
visit. 
</P>
