<HEADLINE> First Asian Bowling Tour to Roll Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The inaugural Asian Bowling
Tour, presented by AMF Bowling Inc., shall represent an
unprecedented series of bowling events to take place over the next
12 months throughout Asia, it was announced here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Tour, which kicks off in March in Malaysia, will comprise
five qualifying tournaments in cities throughout the region and
culminate in the Grand Slam Finals in Taipei next January.
</P>
<P>
The Tour is sanctioned by FIQ-WTBA Asian Zone, the Malaysian
Tenpin Bowling Congress, the Chinese Bowling Association, the
Philippine Bowling Congress, the Hong Kong Tenpin Bowling
Congress, the Singapore Tenpin Bowling Congress and the Chinese
Taipei Bowling Association. The series is promoted by Sports
Corporation Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Tour consists of five Masters Cup events to be held
this year, namely, the Malaysian Masters Cup on March 15-16 in
Petaling Jaya, the China Masters Cup on May 2-3 in Nanjing, the
Philippines Masters Cup on June 13-14 in Manila, the Hong Kong
Masters Cup on July 13-14 and the Singapore Masters Cup on August
17-18. The Grand Slam Finals shall be staged in Taipei on January
16-17 next year.
</P>
<P>
The top 14 Asian men and women bowlers from each Open Men and
Ladies Masters event of the selected International Open will
qualify for the Masters Cup. Each participant will earn Tour
ranking points according to their positions. The top 16 men and
women bowlers from the Tour ranking list at the end of the season
will qualify for the Grand Slam Finals in Taipei.
</P>
<P>
Vivien Fung, president of the FIQ-WTBA Asian Zone, said the
inaugural Tour will help people realize how competitive the sport
of bowling is and it will definitely assist the on-going efforts
to make bowling an Olympic event.  
</P>
</TEXT>
