<HEADLINE> 3 Killed, 3 Wounded in Explosions in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and
three others wounded Friday in a series of bomb explosions in
south Lebanon, local radio Voice of the People reported.
</P>
<P>
Two members of the pro-Israeli South Lebanese Army (SLA) were
killed and two others wounded by bombs planted by Lebanese
resistance fighters in Jezzine, north of the "security Zone" set
up by Israel in south Lebanon, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon's resistance movement has claimed responsibility for
the bomb explosions, and the SLA has admitted the casualties,
according to the radio.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, a Lebanese civilian was killed in a bomb
explosion planted by Israeli troops in the village of Mjdel Zoun
bordering the "security zone," while another was wounded in the
nearby village of Yatril by Israeli artillery shelling.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up the so-called "security zone" in 1985 to
allegedly protect its northern areas from cross-border attacks by
Lebanese guerrillas, who have been fighting to drive the Israelis
out of south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, representatives from the Jezzine area delivered a
letter to Lebanese President Elias Hrawi Friday.
</P>
<P>
The letter called for a halt of using bombs in the conflicts
between Lebanese resistance force and the Israeli troops.
</P>
<P>
It said that bomb explosions always lead to the casualties of
innocent people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
