<DOCNO> XIE19980207.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Leone Junta Alleged to Resume Attack on ECOMOG </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria said Friday that the
military junta has resumed attack against the west African
peace-keeping force known as ECOMOG operating in that troubled
country.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the Nigerian Defense Headquarters
here Friday afternoon said the ECOMOG troops would fight against
"the aggression of the junta" to vigorously defend its positions.
</P>
<P>
The latest development was confirmed by a British Broadcasting
Corporation report monitored here.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, the junta and its cohorts
"resumed the use of land mines, helicopter gunship and gunboats
to prosecute hostilities on ECOMOG and all law abiding citizens
of Sierra Leone at about 17:00 p.m. Thursday".
</P>
<P>
"Meanwhile, the ECOMOG troops have remained steadfast in their
determination to maintain the Conakry Peace Accord but have
resolved to vigorously defend its positions from the aggression
of the junta."
</P>
<P>
Under the peace accord signed last October in Conakry, Guinea,
the junta is to hand over power to ousted president Ahmed Tejan
Kabbah on April 22.
</P>
<P>
But the peace process has been deadlocked as the junta leader,
Johnny Paul Koroma, said it was unrealistic to keep the timetable
with the delay of scheduled disarmament exercise and the failure
to need other requirements of his military regime.
</P>
<P>
The press release, signed by Lt.-Col. Sa Tella, deputy defense
spokesman, also said, "recently more than 100 troops of the junta
defected to ECOMOG positions and pledged their readiness to
cooperate with the whole world and ECOMOG to flush out the junta
and reinstate President Kabbah."
</P>
<P>
Maxwell Kobi, a colonel and ECOMOG commander at Lungi near the
Sierra Leone capital Freetown, said earlier more than 800
soldiers and policemen of the junta had surrendered to ECOMOG.
Many of them with their weapons.
</P>
<P>
According to the BBC, the fighting between the junta forces
and ECOMOG troops is still going on this morning with heavy
shelling across Freetown.
</P>
<P>
A lot of people in military fatigue were seen going up and
down in the town, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Kobi as saying that although the junta forces
resumed their attack this morning, ECOMOG still held its
positions.
</P>
<P>
"They are shelling and we are responding," the ECOMOG
commander said.
</P>
<P>
Refuting report that ECOMOG helicopters going back and forth
at its Lungi base Thursday, transporting the pro-Kabbah civil
defense group known as Kamajors and other things thus starting
the fighting, Kobi said the copters were carrying food stuffs for
ECOMOG troops.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, there are about 4,000 ECOMOG
soldiers stationed near Freetown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
