Benita Ferrero-Wardner in which they discussed regional issues
and bilateral relations between Zimbabwe and Austria.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after the meeting with Mugabe,
Ferrero-Wardner said her first visit to southern Africa was to
strengthen ties and gain an insight into regional issues before
Austria assumes the presidency of the European Union on July 1.
</P>
