<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Hits Afghanistan, 4,000 Feared Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 6 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake in
Afghanistan has left as many as 4,000 people dead and 15,000
homeless, an Afghan embassy official confirmed here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mohammad, Yusef, an official of the Taliban government's
embassy in Pakistan, told Xinhua by telephone Friday night that
the quake hit Afghanistan's Takhor province on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
However, he made no mention of the time and epicenter of the
earthquake.
</P>
<P>
The Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) reported that the quake
was measured 6.1 on the Richter Scale.
</P>
<P>
