<HEADLINE> Water Shortage in Addis Ababa to Be Solved This </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Addis Ababa Water and
Sewerage Services Authority announced Friday that emergency water
supply projects aimed at tackling shortage of water in the
capital city will be completed in July this year.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, Seid
Yimer, an official from the authority, said upon completion of
the 61 million Dollars water supply projects which includes the
underground water supply development and the Dire Dam project, it
could provide 114,000 cubic meters of additional water daily to
the city.
</P>
<P>
Addis Ababa City needs 230,000 cubic meters of water a day and
the current supply stands at 150,000 cubic meters daily only.
However, about 30-40 percent of the 150,000 cubic meters of water
supply is wasted due to dilapidated and faulty pipelines,
according to the authority. 
</P>
