<HEADLINE> Greece's Inflation in January Slightly Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Greece's inflation in January
this year dropped from 4.7 percent in December 1997 to 4.4
percent, the Greek National Statistics Service (NSS) announced
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The NSS attributed this to the drop by 0.8 percent in the
consumer price index (CPI) in January, compared to a 0.5 percent
reduction in the same month of last year.
</P>
<P>
In January, clothing and footwear witnessed a 8.8 percent drop
as well as a 2.9 percent reduction in durable consumer goods and
services because of winter sales.
</P>
<P>
But in the same month, telephone rates rose by 1.2 percent and
tobacco prices by 2.3 percent. 
