<HEADLINE> Edwards Withdraws From English Indoor Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 7 (Xinhua) -- World triple jump record holder
Jonathan Edwards was forced by a flu to withdraw from the English
Indoor Championships after the 60-meter sprint in Birmingham on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Edwards had entered the 60m event and the triple jump in hopes
to win a place in the British team at both events since the meet
served as the British selection trial for the European Indoor
Championships later this month in Valencia, Spain.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Briton holds the outdoor world record for the
triple jump of 18.29 meters.
</P>
<P>
He managed just 6.81 seconds for second place in his
preliminary heat behind Josephus Thomas on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Edwards said he had spoken to the British team selectors to
confirm his wish to enter the triple jump in Valencia. 
