<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Nagoya International Flight Resumes Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 7 (Xinhua) -- An A-340 Airbus took off at
the Shanghai Hongqiao International Airport at 8:50 this morning,
heading for Nagoya, Japan, to mark the resumption of direct
flights between the two cities by the Shanghai-based China Eastern
Airlines.
</P>
<P>
The resumption of the flight is a result of the recent talks
between China and Japan on civil aviation services, according to
official sources.
</P>
<P>
The flight will operate on Wednesdays and Saturdays, using
A-300 or A-340 aircraft. It takes 2 hours and 30 minutes to fly
the 1,604 kilometers between China's largest metropolis and
Japan's third largest city.
</P>
<P>
It is the fifth Japan-bound flight and the 19th international
flight operated by China Eastern.
</P>
<P>
It is also the second Nagoya-bound flight by a Chinese airline
-- the first by China Northwest Airlines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
