outcome of his mission in Baghdad earlier this week aimed at
ending the stand-off that started following Iraq's refusal to
allow U.N. experts to enter presidential sites to carry out
inspections.
</P>
<P>
The stand-off led to a U.S. and British military buildup in the
Gulf to prepare for a military strike against Iraq in case the
ongoing international diplomacy to end the crisis fails.
</P>
<P>
Russia, France and China oppose the use of force against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
France has rejected a recent Iraqi proposal to allow limited
and conditional access to the presidential sites, but Foreign
Minister Hubert Vedrine said the Iraqis have "made a step forward"
and needed to "make additional gestures,"
</P>
<P>
Kuwait is the last leg of Dufourcq's regional tour which also
took him to Egypt, Syria and Saudi Arabia. 
