<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 7 (Xinhua) -- In 1997, the number of
advertising companies in Shanghai, China's largest industrial and
economic center, was reduced by 16 percent to 2,400.
</P>
<P>
More than 600 firms were canceled by local authorities as an
effort to improve the quality of local advertising firms.
</P>
<P>
Last year, however, staff members working in the industry
increased by 0.6 percent to 32,600, and sales climbed by more than
30 percent to top 8.5 billion yuan, or 2.53 percent of the city's
gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the city had 50 foreign-funded advertising
companies with yearly sales of 1.26 billion yuan. 
