<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, February 7 (Xinhua) -- Private high-tech companies have
popped up in Weifang City in east China's Shandong Province, which
is widely known as the "Capital of Kites."
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the city had 752 privately owned high-tech
enterprises, which had fixed assets valued at 1.5 billion yuan and
generated 4 billion yuan in sales and 400 million yuan in pre-tax
profits.
</P>
