<P>
Santer's two-day visit here is part of his first tour in the
Middle East since taking office. He also will visit Israel,
Jordan, Syria, Lebanon and the Palestinian self-rule area.
</P>
<P>
Santer arrived here Friday. He has met with Egyptian Prime
Minister Kamal al-Ganzouri and key representatives of the Egyptian
private sector to discuss Egyptian-European economic cooperation
earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
The two sides are expected to sign financing agreements worth 1
billion Egyptian pounds (294.12 million dollars) within the next
week.
</P>
<P>
In a move to seek European role in solving mounting tensions in
the Gulf over the U.N. inspections of Iraq's suspect biological
and chemical arms, Moussa is to pay a visit to France this week
for talks with his French counterpart Hubert Vedrine.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Ambassador to France Ali Maher told the Voice of Arabs
Radio on Saturday that Cairo and Paris are working together to
find out a diplomatic solution to the U.N.-Iraq standoff in a bid
to avoid the use of force against Iraq as threatened by the
U.S. and Britain.
</P>
<P>
"France plans to maintain its contacts with Baghdad, Cairo,
Moscow as well as other European capitals and the U.S. to give
more chance for solving the crisis peacefully," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
