casualties," Ndahiro said. The enemy withdrew to the Virunga
National Park forests, he asserted.
</P>
<P>
The Friday operation was mounted following tips from local
residents and military intelligence that the enemy had regrouped
in Kagano.
</P>
<P>
Major Ndahiro rejected some media reports that the Ruhengeri
Hospital is submerged by the influx of patients wounded in Kinigi
fighting.
</P>
<P>
"This is incorrect, it is speculative and diversionary," said
the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
In a similar development, another combined operation involving
Rwandan troops deployed in northwestern Gisenyi prefecture took
place targeting Hutu militia hiding in the area on the border
with the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
This operation was also stepped up following tips by local
residents who are fed up with the enemy, said military sources.
</P>
<P>
"The militia had manipulated the Hutu population claiming they
were fighting for their liberation, now they have failed to
deliver what they promised," Ndahiro underscored.
</P>
<P>
The Friday operation in Gisenyi covered the communes of
Rwerere, Mutura, Rubavu, and Nkuli in neighboring Ruhengeri.
</P>
<P>
"We took the enemy by surprise, there was no casualty on our
side," Ndahiro told RNA, adding that the above area covered by
the Volcano forests was the enemy's harbor. 
</P>
