<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Production Means Market Enjoys Sound Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 7 (Xinhua) -- Successful reforms have brought
a steady and healthy development of China's production means
market over the past few years, with a diversified production
means market system emerging throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Sources from a national working conference on goods and
materials held today said that by now China has established nearly
1,000 production means markets involving steel, coal, automobiles,
second-hand motor vehicles and construction materials.
</P>
<P>
These markets include 30 large wholesale markets and 90
regional markets.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the country has also established more than 1,000
auction markets and is steadily proceeding with pilot leasing
markets.
</P>
<P>
A senior official with the Ministry of Internal Trade said at
the conference that the sound development of production means
markets has played a significant role in rationally distributing
resources, guiding production and establishing price
mechanisms. It has also contributed to energizing the local
economy, creating job opportunities and promoting social stability.
</P>
<P>
This year China should continue to strengthen construction and
administration of the production means market, perfect market laws
and standardize market practices, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
