<HEADLINE> Legislative Council Building Open Day in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,000 Hong Kong
people from all walks of life visited the historical Legislative
Council Building in its open day here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan, president of the Provisional Legislative Council,
presided over the opening ceremony to mark the start of the event
Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
She said that the work of the Provisional Legislative Council
has always been made known to the public and most of its meetings
proceeded in an open way. However, this is the first time for
members of the public to visit the building.
</P>
<P>
She expressed the belief that through the visit, Hong Kong
people will have the chance to get a better understanding of how
the Provisional Legislative Council members serve the Hong Kong
citizens.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the Provisional Legislative Council will fulfill
its mission before the end of April this year, Fan said it is her
hope that those eligible people will take an active part in the
first Legislative Council election to be held on May 24 and select
Legislative Council members who will continue their commitment to
the implementation of the Hong Kong Basic Law and the principle of
"one country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, Fan warmly received the first batch of visitors
from Wa Ying College in Kowloon and led them around the chamber
and the antechamber, her office, the dining hall and Provisional
Legislative Council members' rooms as well as conference and press
conference rooms.
</P>
<P>
Other Provisional Legislative Council members including Peggy
P. Lam, Tam Yiu-chung and Henry K. C. Wu were also on hand to play
host to members of the public.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-four middle school students from different parts of Hong
Kong also toured the building. 
</P>
