<HEADLINE> HK to Set Up Committee to Promote Bilingual Legal System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 7 (Xinhua) -- A committee will be set up
soon in Hong Kong to promote the bilingual legal system in the
Special Administrative Region (SAR), a senior government official
said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Elsie Leung, Secretary for Justice of the SAR, said in a Letter
to Hong Kong broadcast on Radio Television Hong Kong Saturday that
the committee will be under her chairmanship and will have wide
terms of reference.
</P>
<P>
"The committee will advise the SAR government on a clear policy
and the long-term goal, and on resource requirements, coordination
of efforts, and the best means to serve the interests of legal
services users," Leung said.
</P>
<P>
In her letter, she noted that the status of Chinese language
usage in the HKSAR has been firmly established in the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Leung said that in the coming year members of the Department of
Justice will improve their capacity to conduct litigation and
prosecutions in the Chinese language.  
</P>
