<HEADLINE> Prices of Precious Metals Fall on India Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 7 (Xinhua) -- Both the prices of gold and
silver fell back on the bullion market here Saturday on lack of
buying support, and closed with notable losses.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold and ornaments lost 35 rupees each at 4,050 and
3,900 rupees (108-104 US dollars) per 10 gram respectively on
fresh arrivals and lower outside advices. Sovereign was also
quoted lower by 25 rupees at 3,525 rupees (94 dollars) per piece
of eight gram.
</P>
<P>
Silver (ready) fell back by 100 rupees to finish at 9,600
rupees (256 dollars) per kilo on reduced offtake. Silver delivery
also moved down from 9,345 to 9,300 rupees (249.2-248 dollars) per
kilo.
</P>
<P>
Marketmen said that a fall in precious metal prices in the
international market and fresh arrivals checked the rising trend
here. They said that buying activities were fewer as most of
marriage season purchases were already made.  
</P>
</TEXT>
