KIEV -- Ukraine appealed to the U.N. and Iraq to take a
cautious attitude toward the weapons inspection crisis in Iraq in
a bid to avert a possible military strike.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian Foreign Ministry said Thursday in a written statement
that all disputes should be resolved through peaceful negotiations
according to international laws and practices.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine hopes that Iraq will unconditionally comply with the
relevant U.N. Security Council resolutions to alleviate the
current situation, and to create an agreeable situation for the
parties concerned to continue peaceful talks. (Ukraine-Iraq)
</P>
