<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 8 Wounded in Clashes in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 7 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli soldier and a
Hezbollah fighter were killed and eight others wounded in a fierce
clash in south Lebanon Saturday morning, local radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The Orient Radio said that the clashes between Israeli troops
and the Iranian-backed Hezbollah guerrillas began at 4:00
a.m. local time in the western sector of the Israeli
self-proclaimed "security zone" in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The radio said that its reporters on the site saw an Israeli
helicopter arrive after the casualties and fail to rescue the four
injuried Israeli soldiers under heavy fire.
</P>
<P>
On Friday night, the radio said, another fierce gun battle
erupted in the central sector of the zone between Israelis and the
Hezbollah, or Party of God. Some 150 shells have landed on nearby
villages. There were no immediate reports of casualties.
</P>
<P>
The Israelis and resistance forces have been embroiled in a war
of attrition Since Israel carved out the 1,200-square-kilometer
security zone in south Lebanon in 1985 with the aim to protect its
north from cross-border attack. 
</P>
