<HEADLINE> Chinese Doctor Examines 42,195 Stomachs by Gastroscope </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 7 (Xinhua) -- A Shanghai doctor has won a
Guinness record for successfully inserting gastroscope into 42,195
stomachs in less than 18 years.
</P>
<P>
Gastroscope is an instrument inserted through the mouth for
visually inspecting the inside of the stomach.
</P>
<P>
Professor Zhang Shanshen, a doctor from Zhongshan Hospital of
Shanghai Medical University, has removed such unusual things as
rings, watches and even chopsticks from the stomachs.
</P>
<P>
The patients Dr. Zhang has examined ranged from 99-year-old
people to one-day-old babies.
</P>
<P>
The longest "foreign body" Dr. Zhang has removed from the
stomach was 20.5 centimeters, and the widest 2.5 centimeters.
</P>
<P>
Zhang's unusual skill has freed the patients from the pains of
going through surgery.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Zhang has also diagnosed 1,920 cases of stomach cancer
through his examinations.
</P>
<P>
A local selection committee has awarded Dr. Zhang the Guinness
record certificate recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
