<DOCNO> XIE19980207.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nairobi Fly Can Be Killed by Pesticides: Expert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 7 (Xinhua) -- Nairobi Fly beetle, the
notorious poisonous insect that causes trouble to local people,
can be killed by common pesticide, a leading Ugandan entomologist
said.
</P>
<P>
Apollo Onapa, an expert in the Health Ministry, told The New
Vision paper Friday that spraying insecticide on breeding sites
such as decomposing leafy materials can stop the propagation of
the insect.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time local authority acknowledged the
presence of the insect.
</P>
<P>
The poisonous insect relieves an substance on human body that
causes swellings or blisters and pain on skin. But local doctors
assured that the insect did not constitute a threat to the life
of patients. Patients usually recover within two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The number of insect increases rapidly due to excessive El
Nino rains in the city since last Christmas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
