<HEADLINE> Comaneci Honored Flo Hyman Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Former world gymnastics
legend Nadia Comaneci was honored the Flo Hyman Award for 1998 in
a ceremony in the United States on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Comaneci, now of U.S. nationality, received the award from the
Women Sports Federation, Romania's Mediafax News Agency reported
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Comaneci, representing Romania then, was the first ever gymnast
who was awarded a perfect 10-point in the sports history and she
rose to stardom after winning the uneven bars, beam and all-round
titles at the Olympic Games in Montreal, Canada, in 1976.
</P>
<P>
The award was named after American women's volleyball player
Flo Hyman who died of heart problems in a 1986 match in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Past winners include tennis players Chris Evert, Martina
Navratilova and athlete Jackie Joyner-Kersee. 
