<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 7 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia exported over 500
million U.S. Dollars during last fiscal year ending last July,
registering a 25 percent increase compared to the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to an article carried on Saturday's Ethiopian
Herald, the increase was attributed to the prevailing favorable
condition in the country, the increment of export items in
quality and quantity and the rise in price of coffee in the world
market.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's export goods include coffee, hides and skins,
livestock and meat, pulses and oilseeds, beeswax, horticulture,
textile products and others.
</P>
<P>
During the last fiscal year, coffee accounts for 67 percent of
the export, hides and skins for 12 percent, pulses and oilseeds
for seven percent, chat for five percent and other items for nine
percent.
</P>
<P>
To boost the export trade of the country, the Ethiopian
government is doing its best to help exporters to become
competitive in the international market by improving their
products both in quality and quantity.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia plans to launch a program aimed at boosting the
supply of meat, hides and skins to the world market in later part
of this year, according to the article. 
</P>
