<HEADLINE> Breitling Orbiter-2 Balloon Lands in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 7 (Xinhua) -- The Breitling Orbiter-2 Balloon
with the crew of three Europeans landed at 0930 local time
Saturday morning in Okpo, Bago division of Myanmar, 155 kilometers
from Yangon.
</P>
<P>
The ballooning trio have beat the 12-year-old world record for
the longest non-stop flight without refuelling.
</P>
<P>
