<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 7 (Xinhua) -- The German government is
scheduled to hold a three-day meeting in Nairobi to seek possible
solutions to problems in the Great Lakes region, the Daily Nation
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the meeting starting from Monday would be
chaired by German Vice-Foreign Minister Wemer Hoyer and German
ambassadors from the Lakes region and four Members of Parliament
would attend the meeting.
</P>
