<HEADLINE> Severe Cold Hits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 7 (Xinhua) -- Severe cold spell will continue
to hit Vietnam's northern and central areas next week, the
National Meteorological Center predicted on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to the prediction, the cold weather will not abate
until the middle of this month.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, an unexpected 12-day cold spell, affecting the
northern and central provinces, brought the average
temperature down to 10 to 11 degrees Celsius.
</P>
<P>
The temperature in northern mountainous areas lowed to five to seven
degrees, nine to 11 degrees in the river deltas and 12 to 14 degrees
along the central coast.
</P>
<P>
The cold spell has caused light rain and drizzle in northern
and central provinces.
</P>
<P>
Light rains during the cold has lessened droughts which
have struck the province of Quang Ngai in the north. 
</P>
