<HEADLINE> China to Solve Environmental Problem by 2020: Top Scientist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 7 (Xinhua) -- China plans to solve its
environmental problems by the year 2020, said a top Chinese
scientist in an article carried on today's People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
Scientists of natural and social sciences will work hand in
hand to find solutions to problems related to energy, resources,
environment, ecology, and transportation around the year 2020,
said Lu Yongxiang, President of the Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS), the country's top natural science research body.
</P>
<P>
The problems will surely hinder China's future development, and
Chinese scientists should serve the country's sustained growth by
devoting to study on energy, environmental and ecological issues,
Lu noted in a lengthy article published by the country's leading
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
China has to face the overall test of international competition
and cooperation under the circumstances of globalization of
science and economy.
</P>
<P>
Lu, also a CAS academician, said that in 2050 medium-developed
countries will enter a post-industrialization society featured
with the knowledge-oriented economy in 2050. China must follow a
growth orbit of intensive development due to the precondition of
shortage of energy, resources and relevantly fragile
eco-environment.
</P>
<P>
Another article carried on the newspaper said that even though
China has abundant resources, every Chinese only shares 28.1
percent of fresh water, 32.3 percent of arable land, 14.3 percent
of forest, and 32.3 percent of grassland of the average shared by
the people in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
