striking a powerful counterblow should an invasion occur.
</P>
<P>
Another report quoted a Russian Defense Ministry spokesman as
saying Friday that Russia's strategic arms are not in a state of
high-level combat readiness.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the possible use of tactical nuclear weapons by
the U.S. against Iraq, the spokesman said Russia's strategic
missile, air and submarine forces are still on regular duty.
</P>
<P>
Russia's intercontinental ballistic missiles, however, are not
in launch status, he added.
</P>
<P>
Russia strongly opposes the use of force in the Iraqi
crisis. Russian President Boris Yeltsin has warned that launching
a military attack on Iraq could ignite another international
confrontation. 
