<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia and
Briton Greg Rusedski reached the semifinals of the Croatian Indoor
tennis tournament in Split, Croatia on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded Ivanisevic beat Czech Jiri Novak 7-6 (7-5),
7-6 (11-9) while Rusedski defeated Martin Damm of the Czech
Republic 6-1, 6-4 in the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
The seventh-seeded Novak gave Ivanisevic trouble from the
beginning, leading the first set 3-1.
</P>
<P>
