led again at 2-0.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic won six of the following seven points before winning
the set on his third set point with an ace.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Novak had a chance for a break at 4-3 but
Ivanisevic hit two aces in a row, then won the game.
</P>
<P>
The tiebreaker was spiced with the unexpected burst of rage by
Ivanisevic, who smashed his racket to vent his dissatisfaction
toward his own performance.
</P>
<P>
In the other quarterfinals, fifth seed Marc Rosset of
Switzerland downed Rainer Schuttler of Germany 6-2, 6-2, and
Martin Sinner of Germany defeated Kenneth Carlsen of Denmark 5-7,
6-3, 7-6 (7-0).
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's semifinals, Rusedski meets Rosset and Ivanisevic
faces Sinner. 
