<HEADLINE> China Among Ten Biggest Traders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 7 (Xinhua) -- China ranked 10th in the world
in terms of foreign trade volume in 1997, with its imports and
exports totaling 325 billion US dollars, according to today's
International Business Daily.
</P>
<P>
After staying at the 11th place for five years running, China
exceeded Belgium-Luxembourg for the first time to enter the list
of the top ten traders in 1997, said the daily, which quoted
statistics by the World Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
China's exports stood at the 10th place, totaling 182.7 billion
US dollars; and imports, 12th, 142.3 billion dollars, the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
China's Hong Kong Special Administrative Region and Taiwan
province ranked seventh and 14th, respectively, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
