<DOCNO> XIE19980207.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Foreign Exchange Reserves at 19B Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's foreign exchange
reserves at the end of January 1998 amounted to 19.063 billion
U.S. dollars, sufficient to import non-oil commodities for 4.7
months, Bank Indonesia, the central bank, said.
</P>
<P>
The central bank also has a standby loan of 1.873 billion
dollars until the end of January, local press Saturday quoted the
bank sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the 21.418 billion dollars at the end of December
1997, the foreign exchange consisting of gross overseas assets by
the end of January 1998 declined by 10.9 percent, and continued to
decline from the 25.528 billion dollars at the end of December
1996.
</P>
<P>
The foreign exchange reserves consist of bank foreign exchange
deposited at Bank Indonesia under the compulsory Minimum Giro
Scheme, foreign currencies, time export draft, and others,
previously not included as Official Foreign Exchange Reserves.
</P>
</TEXT>
