<HEADLINE> Following are quotes of some participants at the Nagano Olympic Winter Games which starts on Saturday: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"When I asked my father if Iculd do Alpine skiing, he said it was
too dangerous. When I asked if I could do freestyle, he said yes
because he didn't know what it was." -- American freestyle moguls
skier Liz McIntyre, on how she got into the sport
</P>
<P>
"He gets pretty excited about fishing." -- Canadian coach Derrick
Auch, on whether speedskater Jeremy Wotherspoon ever gets worked up
about anything.
</P>
<P>
"I think we did well. Usually, it's 15-0." -- Wally Kozak,
assistant coach of the Japanese women's ice hockey team, on their 10-0
loss to the United States inan exhibition game.
</P>
<P>
