<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Late Surge Improves Italy's Industrial Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Italy's industrial production
increased by 2.2 percent last year, reversing the decline of 1996,
largely due to a surge in December, Italy's statistics bureau
Istat reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Production in the last month of 1997 was 8.1 percent higher
than the same month a year earlier, Istat said. In 1996,
production fell by 1.7 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Italian industry outdid itself in almost all fields in 1997,
despite holidays which cut down the number of hours worked.
</P>
<P>
As compared with the same month in 1996, transportation
manufacturing was up 31.5 percent in December 1997, non-metallic
minerals manufacturing was up 18.6 percent, rubber and plastic
materials manufacturing up 16.4 percent, and the production of
metal and wood products up 14.9 percent, while chemicals and
synthetic fibers production increased 10.2 percent, and textiles
and clothing rose 9 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, optics and electronics were down 5 percent from
December 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
