<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 7 (Xinhua) -- The following are highlights of
today's major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Jiang Zemin, Chinese president and general secretary of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, has express
deep concern for those who fell ill and died from drinking
unlawfully made alcohol in north China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 people died and hundreds were hospitalized in Shuozhou
after drinking the poisonous alcoholic beverages during the Spring
Festival. Jiang has instructed legal departments to severely
punish lawbreakers who have been involved in making and dealing in
illegal alcoholic drinks.
</P>
<P>
-- The Deputies Qualifications Examination Committee of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC)
examined and confirmed yesterday the qualifications of 2,980
deputies to the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- A cook reputed as "the world's best chef," a locomotive
driver with no accident record in his 20-plus-year career, and
eight other workers received here today the country's top award
for skilled workers -- the China Grand Prize for Professional
Skills.
</P>
<P>
The ten award winners were also given a chance to meet Premier
Li Peng in Zhongnanhai, China's central government compound,
before Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo bestowed each of them with a medal
made of 50 grams of pure gold. The medal was engraved with an
inscription from President Jiang Zemin: "National Model Skilled
Worker."
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Li Peng will pay an official friendly visit
to Russia from February 17 to 18. He will also pay an official
friendly visit to Luxembourg and the Netherlands sequently
starting on February 12.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Li Peng presided over a discussion in Beijing
yesterday to consult leaders of non-Communist parties and
noted figures with no party-affiliation on the draft of the
government work report to be submitted to the upcoming First
Session of the Ninth National People's Congress, due on March 5.
</P>
<P>
-- Governments at all levels should focus their efforts on
improving social security and public welfare, in tandem with
ongoing economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
Tackling tasks such as economic system reconstruction, reform
on state-owned enterprises, and improving governmental functions
involves looking for solutions to problems affecting public life
and social benefits, said Chen Jinhua, minister in charge of the
State Planning Commission, yesterday in Beijing. 
</P>
