<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, February 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Secretary of Iran's Constitutional Guardian Council
Ayatollah Ali Jannati warned here Friday that Iraq's neighbors
would not allow any military strike on Baghdad, the Iranian
official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Friday prayers congregations, Jannati
criticized the behavior of the U.S. government toward Baghdad and
the U.S. handling of the issue of the U.N. arms inspections in
Iraq. (Iran-Iraq-Military Strike)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France has proposed that Iraq be allowed to import oil
equipment to increase and improve its oil output, said Foreign
Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"France has presented a draft resolution and discussions are
under way (at the U.N. Security Council)," she said.
</P>
<P>
The proposal serves part of the drafted enlargement of the "Oil
for Food" program with Iraq, said the spokeswoman.
(France-Iraq-Proposal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TAIYUAN, China -- Two suspects have been arrested and 33 others
detained for their involvement in the poisonous alcohol case in
north China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
According to local police, an illegal wine-maker in Wenshui
County produced the fatal drinks by mixing 2,400 kilograms of
methanol with 24,000 kilograms of alcohol and sold the mixture.
</P>
<P>
The buyer then mixed the dangerous drinks with other additives
and wholesaled it to private shops in Shuozhou and Datong cities.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, 222 people were hospitalized from drinking the
mixture; 27 people have died, while 171 have been discharged from
hospitals. (China-Poisonous-Alcohol-Suspects)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japan's Okinawa Prefecture Governor Masahide Ota on
Friday rejected the central government's proposal to build an
offshore heliport for U.S. military forces.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in Haha, capital of Okinawa, Ota stressed
that the residents of Nago, the proposed site of the heliport,
voted overwhelmingly against the project in a non-binding
referendum held last December.
</P>
<P>
The governor even expressed his opposition to U.S. military
presence in Japan, adding that if the heliport plan was permitted,
it meant to allow the United States to establish its military
bases on Japan's territory. (Japan-Okinawa-US Heliport)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- British Defense Secretary George Robertson announced
here Friday that Britain would send eight Tornado aircraft to the
Gulf region within the next few days to beef up British military
presence in the region.
</P>
<P>
Robertson said in a written answer to the British parliament
that the government made the decision following a review of
Britain's military presence in the Gulf "in view of the continuing
refusal of the Iraqi regime to comply fully with the requirements
of the United Nations Security Council." (UK-Gulf-Fighters)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MADRID -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing on Friday urged
Chinese and Spanish businesses to strengthen their cooperation so
as to bring bilateral economic and trade relations to a new level.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to more than 300 Spanish businessmen, Li said that the
good political relations between the two countries have provided
the conditions for their friendly cooperation in every fields.
</P>
<P>
He said that there is a great potential for closer bilateral
economic and trade cooperation. He hoped the business community
will fully tap it. (Spain-China-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin reiterated that the
security of Europe should be ensured by Europeans themselves, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Russia will pursue such a policy despite the dislike of some
people, the president said Thursday in an interview with Russian
and Italian journalists in the Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin was also optimistic about his coming visit to Italy,
scheduled to start on February 9.
</P>
<P>
The visit, which will mainly aim at improving relations with
Italy, its second largest trading partner in Europe, will not be
pointless, said the president. (Russia-Italy-Yeltsin)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- A strong earthquake jolted northern Afghanistan
this week, leaving at least 3,200 people dead and thousands of
others homeless, the Taliban's ambassador to Pakistan and embassy
officials confirmed here late Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Maulawi Dilawar told Xinhua by telephone that the quake, which
measured 6.1 on the Richter Scale, hit the country's northern
Takhor province Wednesday. (Afghanistan-Quake-Casualties-1stlead)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey's leftist parties held demonstrations here
Friday to protest the aggressive policy of the United States
toward Iraq, local TV reported.
</P>
<P>
Supporters of Turkey's Labor Party, People's Democratic Party
as well as Freedom and Solidarity Party shouted slogans of "U.S.
hands off the Middle East," "Yankees go home," and "Down with
American imperialism" in front of U.S. Embassy here.
</P>
<P>
Haydar Eiker from the Freedom and Solidarity Party delivered a
speech at the rally. He said the real goal of the U.S. is only to
consolidate its dominance in the oil-rich Gulf region.
(Turkey-Protest-US)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton Friday said that he
would "never" consider resigning over the alleged sex scandal.
</P>
<P>
At a joint news conference with British Prime Minister Tony
Blair, Clinton once again refused to give detailed explanation
about the issue. He has repeatedly denied having a sexual
relationship with former white house intern Monica Lewinsky and
encouraging her to lie under oath about it. (US-Clinton-Intern)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Bosnia-Herzegovina's new national flag was
seen Friday flying in front of the U.N. Secretariat Building.
</P>
<P>
The new flag consists of a large golden triangle against a blue
background, with a line of white stars along one of the triangle's
sides.
</P>
<P>
The triangle symbolizes the three constituent people of
Bosnia-Herzegovina, the yellow stands for the sun as a symbol of
hope, while the blue and the stars represents Europe, of which the
country is a part. (Bosnia-New Flag-UN)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Two U.S. Marine Corps F-18 fighter jets collided
in mid-air and crashed in the Persian Gulf on Friday during a
training exercise, killing one of the two pilots, the Defense
Department said.
</P>
<P>
The pilots of the two single-seat fighter jets, based on board
the aircraft carrier George Washington, were picked up by search
and rescue units and returned to the ship.
</P>
<P>
But one of the two pilots died and the other is in good
condition, the Defense Department said. (US-Iraq-Jet Collision)
</P>
