<HEADLINE> Brazilian Vicepresident Visits Holland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, February 7 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Vicepresident Marco
Maciel started a three-day visit to Holland on Saturday, said
an official source.
</P>
<P>
Maciel will take part in a seminar on the Brazilian economy
outlook to be held in Amsterdam, the Dutch capital, and will
contact executives of firms of that nation.
</P>
<P>
He will also meet with Dutch Prime Minister Wim Kok,
Vicepresident Hans Dijkstal, and Finance Minister Gerrit
Zalm.
</P>
<P>
The vicepresident is the highest ranking Brazilian
official to ever visit Holland. Maciel's trip has a very important
meaning for the preparation of the Latin America, the Caribbean,
and the European Union summit conference to be held in the first
semester of 1999 in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Holland is now the fifth biggest European investor in Brazil.
Brazil received last year 2.5 billion dollars in direct investment
from Holland. 
