<HEADLINE> Brazilian Crude Oil, Gas Reserves Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, Februray 6 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's total crude
oil and natural gas reserves increased 20 percent in 1997,
compared to those of 1996, announced the state firm Petroleos de
Brazil (Petrobras).
</P>
<P>
The reserves, including probable and proved, increased from
14.1 billion equivalent oil barrels in 1996, to 16.9 billion
barrels in 1997, according to Petrobras.
</P>
<P>
The new figure was approved Thursday by the Petrobras board of
directors.
</P>
<P>
Proved reserves increased 4.9 percent when they went from 8.1
billion barrels in 1996, to 8.5 billion barrels at the end of last
year. 
