<HEADLINE> Peruvian Exports To Asia Stabilized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian exports to Asia reaching
a total of 1.358 billion U.S. dollars kept stable in 1997, despite
the region's financial crisis, according to the National Customs
Superintendence authorities.
</P>
<P>
Peruvian exports to Asia were 20 percent of the total volume of
exports last year, worth 741 million dollars. Eighty percent of
Peruvian exports to Asia were raw materials.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan were the two main Asian markets for the
Peruvian products, absorbing 70 percent of Peruvian goods sent to
the region.
</P>
<P>
Peruvian exporters said that the Asian economic crisis did not
impair the sales to that region.
</P>
<P>
Seventy percent of fish meal exports and 50 percent of copper
were directed to Asia, and they are the main products of export to
that zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
