<HEADLINE> Minister: Chilean Economic Growth Stunned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Chile will redude this year
its rate of growth because of the Asian financial crisis that
upset the world economy, said Economy Minister Alvaro Garcia.
</P>
<P>
The economic growth projections in 1998 of 6.5 percent and
seven percent must be revised downward to between 0.7 percent and
one percent, said Garcia.
</P>
<P>
"All the (international) diagnoses agree that the world economy
will reduce its rate of growth to between 0.7 and one percent,"
said the minister.
</P>
<P>
"I think that for an economy as open as the Chilean one, we
should expect effects of that magnitude," he added.
</P>
<P>
The minister also predicted that the rhythm of creation of jobs
will be down as a result of exports income drop.
</P>
<P>
Garcila said that the recent rise in the interbank interest
rates in Chile was aimed at preventing financial uncertainty in
the country and to contain the expansion of spending, particularly
from the private sector. 
</P>
