<HEADLINE> UN Headquarters Sees Bosnia's New Flag </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Bosnia-Herzegovina's new
national flag was seen today flying in front of the UN Secretariat
Building.
</P>
<P>
The new flag consists of a large golden triangle against a blue
background, with a line of white stars along one of the triangle's
sides.
</P>
<P>
The triangle symbolizes the three constituent people of
Bosnia-Herzegovina, the yellow stands for the sun as a symbol of
hope, while the blue and the stars represents Europe, of which the
country is a part.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the ceremony of raising the new flag, UN
secretary-General Kofi Annan said no conflict or cause had
presented a greater challenge to the United Nations, which sent
personnel from all parts of the world to the region to promote the
peace and unity achieved today.
</P>
<P>
The UN chief said they did so for the sake of the people of
Bosnia and in the hope that coexistence. once flourishing among
the communities of that country, could once again become reality.
</P>
<P>
Muhamad Sacirbey, Bosnian UN Ambassador, noted that the new
flag was already flying in front of the Presidency building in
Sarajevo and it would also fly at the Winter Olympics at Nagano,
Japan.  
</P>
