<HEADLINE> European Commission President Starts Mideast Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 6 (Xinhua) -- European Commission President
Jacques Santer arrived here Friday night, starting a multi-leg
tour of the Middle East region, the Middle East News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Upon arrival at the airport, Santer told reporters that his
current tour is aimed at tackling the latest developments of the
regional situation, the European role in this respect and
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He voiced concern over the lack of progress in the Middle East
peace process, and stressed the necessity to achieve a just and
comprehensive peace between Israel and its Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the standoff over arms inspections between Iraq
and the United Nations Special Commission in charge of eliminating
Iraq's weapons of mass destruction, Santer said that Iraq must
respect the U.N. Security Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa, who greeted Santer at the
airport, said that Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak will meet with
Santer Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Moussa said that he will hold talks with Santer Friday night on
the Mideast peace process and the European role in this field.
</P>
<P>
He added that they will also discuss the developments of the
Iraqi crisis and the Egyptian-European partnership.
</P>
<P>
After wrapping up his visit here, Santer will also travel to
Israel, Syria and Jordan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
